Definition: mentally acute or penetratingly discerning
Example: too clear-eyed not to see what problems would follow; chaos could be prevented only by clear-sighted leadership; much too perspicacious to be taken in by so spurious an argument
Synonyms: clear-sighted, perspicacious, noun, cognition, perspicaciousness, mentally, acute, or, penetratingly, discerning, too, not, to, see, what, problems, would, follow, chaos, could, be, prevented, only, by, leadership, much, taken, in, so, spurious, an, argument
Category: adj.all
